  "prompt": "How do I know who is following me on Snapchat?",
  "response": "To see who is following you on Snapchat, you can follow these steps:\n\n1. **Open Snapchat**: Launch the Snapchat app on your device.\n\n2. **Go to Your Profile**: Tap on your Bitmoji or the circular profile icon in the top left corner of the camera screen to access your profile.\n\n3. **View Your Friends List**: Tap on \"My Friends\" to see a list of all your friends on Snapchat. Anyone who is following you and has added you back will appear here.\n\n4. **Check Your Snap Score**: If you're interested in seeing who has added you, you can also access your Snap Score by tapping on your profile icon again, which can indicate who has added or followed you.\n\n5. **Add Friends**: If you see people who you haven't added back, you can search for them via the \"Add Friends\" feature to see their profiles and if they are following you.\n\n6. **Notifications**: Occasionally, when someone adds you, you might receive a notification. Make sure to check your notifications for any alerts about new friends or followers.\n\nRemember, Snapchat does not have a public \"followers\" list like some other social media platforms, so the best way to see who is following you is through your friends list.",
